title: "Notes on new C# features"
date: 2014-5-24
comments: false
categories: c#, .NET
---

* Field parameters
* initializers for auto properties

```csharp

public class SecurityClearance
{
  public string Level {get; set;} = "Baseline" 
}
```
* Explicit constructors: pass parameters to a primary constructor with 'this(x,y)'

* Passing params to base constructor now easier: Customer : CustomerBase(name)

* Declaration expressions

```csharp
if (int.TryParse(s, out int i)) { … } 
GetCoordinates(out var x, out var y); 
Console.WriteLine("Result: {0}", (int x = GetValue()) * x); 
if ((string s = o as string) != null) { … s … } 
```csharp

* Exception filters

```csharp
try { … } 
catch (MyException e) if (myfilter(e)) 
{ 
 … 
}
```

* Element initialisers

```csharp

var numbers = new Dictionary<int, string> { 
 [7] = "seven", 
 [9] = "nine", 
 [13] = "thirteen" 
};

var customer = new JsonData { 
 $first = "Anders", // => ["first"] = "Anders" 
 $last = "Hejlsberg" // => ["last"] = "Hejlsberg" 
} 

string first = customer.$first; // => customer["first"] 

```




